      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Self-treating a painful, red eye with over-the-counter antibiotics or ointment without a diagnosis is dangerous because many types of eye infections, like viral or allergic conjunctivitis, will not respond to antibiotics and could become worse. Using the wrong medication can also lead to resistance or mask symptoms of a more serious underlying issue like a corneal scratch or infection. The cost and time of a proper diagnosis are far cheaper than the potential cost of permanent vision damage or spreading an infection to your other eye.",
      "source": "target",
